The Virology Testing Market is segmented based on product type, application, and end user. In terms of product type, the market is categorized into molecular assays, immunoassays, rapid tests, and others. Molecular assays are widely used for their high sensitivity and accuracy in detecting viral genetic material. Immunoassays, on the other hand, detect antibodies produced by the immune system in response to viral infections. Rapid tests are gaining popularity due to their quick turnaround time, making them ideal for point-of-care testing. In terms of application, virology testing is essential for Hepatitis, HIV, Influenza, Tropical diseases, COVID-19, and other viral infections. The end users of virology testing include hospitals, diagnostic laboratories, research institutes, and others.

